---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";
import Main from "@/layouts/Main.astro";
import { SITE } from "@/config";
---

<Layout title={`Projects | ${SITE.title}`}>
  <Header />
  <Main
    pageTitle="Projects"
    pageDesc="A selection of projects I've built — spanning full-stack web apps, backend systems, and team collaborations."
  >
    <ul class="space-y-6">
      <li class="border border-border rounded-lg p-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Surfboard Rental Management System</h2>
        <p class="mt-0.5 text-xs text-foreground/50">
          Individual full-stack project
        </p>

        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-foreground/80">
          A full-stack rental management system covering booking, inventory management,
          and authentication workflows. I built the Spring Boot REST API using a layered
          backend structure, Dockerised the backend deployment, and deployed the frontend
          separately.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-foreground/60">
          Java · Spring Boot · REST APIs · Docker · Render · Vercel
        </p>

        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">Highlights</h3>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-sm text-foreground/80 space-y-1">
            <li>Designed backend API endpoints for rental and inventory workflows.</li>
            <li>Structured the backend using controller, service, and repository layers.</li>
            <li>Added validation and exception handling for API requests.</li>
            <li>Deployed the backend and frontend as separate application components.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-4 flex gap-3">
          <a
            href="https://surfboard-rental-management.vercel.app"
            class="text-sm text-accent hover:underline"
          >
            Live Demo →
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/zxl3011/surfboard-rental-management"
            class="text-sm text-accent hover:underline"
          >
            GitHub →
          </a>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="border border-border rounded-lg p-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">StitchFlow</h2>
        <p class="mt-0.5 text-xs text-foreground/50">
          Individual full-stack project · OpenAI Build Week 2026
        </p>

        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-foreground/80">
          A local-first workflow and progress management tool for knitters and
          crocheters working across patterns with inconsistent terminology and
          structure. StitchFlow turns a pattern into an editable hierarchy and
          records the exact row, round, step, and stitch where a maker stopped.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-foreground/60">
          TypeScript · React · Next.js / vinext · Vite · Tailwind CSS · Cloudflare · OpenAI Sites · localStorage
        </p>

        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">Highlights</h3>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-sm text-foreground/80 space-y-1">
            <li>Modelled patterns as editable Project, Section, Part, Row, Round, and Step hierarchies.</li>
            <li>Implemented stitch-level progress tracking with sequential completion inference and full manual override.</li>
            <li>Added US, UK, and Japanese terminology support alongside English and Simplified Chinese interfaces.</li>
            <li>Kept project data and image attachments device-local, with no login, cloud sync, or runtime API cost.</li>
            <li>Built accessibility and appearance controls plus a compact browser-native print-to-PDF layout.</li>
            <li>Used Codex with GPT-5.6 Sol as a transparent implementation and reasoning partner during Build Week.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a
            href="https://stitchflow-agent.crafty-cedar-1657.chatgpt.site/"
            class="text-sm text-accent hover:underline"
          >
            Live Demo →
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/zxl3011/stitchflow-agent/tree/codex/build-week-2026"
            class="text-sm text-accent hover:underline"
          >
            GitHub →
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://youtu.be/x8B2VpBRKBw"
            class="text-sm text-accent hover:underline"
          >
            Video Demo →
          </a>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="border border-border rounded-lg p-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Workforce Time Management System</h2>
        <p class="mt-0.5 text-xs text-foreground/50">
          Team backend project · Code not public
        </p>

        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-foreground/80">
          A workforce management backend system built with Java Spring Boot and MySQL.
          The system supports staff administration, salary records, standard working hours,
          overtime rules, penalty configuration, and role-based access control data.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-foreground/60">
          Java · Spring Boot · MySQL · REST APIs · Azure DevOps · Postman
        </p>

        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">My Contributions</h3>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-sm text-foreground/80 space-y-1">
            <li>Developed backend APIs for staff administration.</li>
            <li>Implemented salary history logic so new pay rates apply only to future records.</li>
            <li>Added support for staff standard working hours and validation rules.</li>
            <li>Built and collaborated on configuration APIs for overtime and penalty settings.</li>
            <li>Worked on role data and role endpoints to support authentication and access control.</li>
            <li>Tested backend endpoints with Postman and coordinated API contracts with frontend teammates.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="border border-border rounded-lg p-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Indigenous Art Atlas</h2>
        <p class="mt-0.5 text-xs text-foreground/50">
          Team full-stack project · Code not public
        </p>

        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-foreground/80">
          An interactive web application for exploring Indigenous artworks on a map.
          The platform used Leaflet.js on the frontend and a PHP/MySQL backend to manage
          users, artwork data, artist profiles, collections, and access-controlled views.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-foreground/60">
          PHP · MySQL · JavaScript · Leaflet.js · Role-based access
        </p>

        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">My Contributions</h3>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-sm text-foreground/80 space-y-1">
            <li>Implemented user registration, login, sessions, and role-based navigation.</li>
            <li>Built artist profile and artist application workflows.</li>
            <li>Developed user collection and favourite artwork features.</li>
            <li>Used prepared statements for safer database access.</li>
            <li>Integrated backend data with frontend pages and dynamic user views.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-4 flex gap-3">
          <a
            href="https://indigenous-art-atlas.onrender.com"
            class="text-sm text-accent hover:underline"
          >
            Live Demo →
          </a>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </Main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
